President Obama will host a meeting with The Prince of Wales and The Duchess of Cornwall in the Oval Office on March 19. The Vice President will also be present at the meeting. The Prince and Duchess will be visiting the United States from March 17-20 to promote the partnership between the UK and the US in areas such as combatting climate change, creating opportunities for youth, encouraging corporate social responsibility, and preserving historical and cultural links. During their visit, they will also be visiting Mt. Vernon, the Armed Forces Retirement Home, and the National Archives, where The Prince will commemorate the 800th anniversary of Magna Carta. This visit highlights the special relationship between the United States and the United Kingdom.